                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119P43/780: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-08T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1919, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3709. For Polk. Referring to your 5071 of November 7, 4 p.m. You are authorized
                    to give Crillon servants 30 days’ notice. You will proceed on theory that the
                    whole Mission will return home on or about December 1, with the exception of
                    those Embassy may need to carry on pending matters which remain. I see no reason
                    why Bliss and White should not return with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
